{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_1","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '52,92p' .claude/plans/active-codex-managed-agent-roadmap.md\"","aggregated_output":"### Milestone 3 — Insight and Guidance Layer\nStatus: active\n\nTargets:\n- stabilize usage report generation\n- improve topic map / word cloud / weekly shift interaction\n- make guidance more actionable and durable\n\nAudit findings:\n- host-side insights fallback already reads a persisted usage report from `~/.codex/codex_managed_agent_usage_report.json`\n- webview UI state persists topic-driven navigation state through `vscode.setState()`\n- first bounded reliability gap: persisted `topicFocus` is not revalidated against current insights data or current threads after reload\n- host-side persisted-report fallback is sufficient for webview reload recovery; a second reload-survivable webview cache would be redundant right now\n\nCompleted in this milestone:\n- persisted `topicFocus` is now cleared on reload when current thread data no longer supports the saved insight navigation state\n- active-session insights rendering now reuses the last usable report payload when a transient refresh arrives empty\n- insights UI now explicitly discloses when it is showing persisted fallback data or an in-session cached report\n- insights disclosure now includes a freshness timestamp for persisted fallback data and in-session cached reports\n- persisted fallback insights now get explicit stale wording once the cached report is older than a simple 24-hour threshold\n- topic-map-driven thread filtering now exposes an explicit clear-focus action directly in the thread summary surface\n- active `topicFocus` now highlights the matching topic-map node so the filtered target stays visually legible\n\nExit review:\n- current insights persistence/disclosure flow now covers reload fallback, in-session cache reuse, source disclosure, freshness disclosure, and stale wording\n- topic-map/thread-list linkage now covers click-to-filter, reload-safe focus validation, explicit clear-focus, and active-node highlighting\n- next smallest Milestone 3 gap is weekly-report actionability: the panel summarizes deltas, but it still lacks one concise next-action cue\n\nCurrent bounded slice:\n- add one concise next-action cue to the weekly report surface\n\n### Milestone 4 — Operational Reliability\nStatus: pending\n\nTargets:\n- background continue observability\n- clear loop status semantics\n- degraded-state handling\n- linked-vs-running distinction across surfaces\n\n### Milestone 5 — Publishable Product Quality\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
